This article is a press briefing transcript from the White House, featuring Press Secretary Jay Carney and Department of Homeland Security Secretary Janet Napolitano. The briefing discusses the effects of sequestration on the Department of Homeland Security and the impacts it would have on national security and the economy. Secretary Napolitano explains that the automatic budget reduction mandated by sequestration would be disruptive and destructive to the nation's security and economy. She outlines the specific impacts on her department, including furloughs of customs and border protection officers, longer wait times at airports and border crossings, reduced presence in the Arctic by the Coast Guard, and reductions in disaster relief and homeland security grant funding. Secretary Napolitano emphasizes the need for Congress to prevent sequestration in order to maintain the safety, security, and resiliency of the country.